From 3b4d83fc37458481a2f9e77f9edc3749925ae1f7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dev <dev@local>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 00:25:14 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Production hardening: fix FAISS query off-by-one + lock
 deadlock, wire persisted index into retrieval, BM25/hybrid search, MCP
 server, real CI
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- FAISS query() resolved hits by list position while the index stores numeric
  ids from 1 — every semantic result was the wrong chunk. Now resolved via
  reverse idmap (correct after removals too).
- remove()/compact() deadlocked: exclusive flock re-acquired via nested
  _load()/rebuild() on a new fd. Lock is now re-entrant per process.
- Retrieval loads the persisted FAISS index and encodes only the query,
  instead of re-embedding the whole corpus per search.
- BM25 (new default) with identifier-splitting tokenizer; hybrid BM25+
  embeddings via reciprocal rank fusion.
- Token budget is a hard ceiling (two-phase selection w/ truncation fallback).
- MCP server: xkit mcp <project> exposes retrieve_context/update_index/
  index_project/get_metrics to Claude Code, Cline, Cursor.
- Tree-sitter chunking via prebuilt wheels; AST splits at symbol boundaries
  and line-splits oversized functions. Cached tiktoken encoder. Stale-vector
  cleanup on update. Capped metrics history. Skip >2MB files.
- CI actually fails on test failures now; Linux/macOS/Windows matrix; ruff.
- Repo hygiene: LICENSE (MIT), .gitignore, removed __pycache__/.DS_Store/
  stray bundle/no-op workflows; registered broken CLI subcommands; fixed
  missing shutil import.
